1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,760
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:01:40,880 --> 00:01:44,360
So… does that mean you’re all better now? Then let’s go check out my secret.

3
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:50,479
I decided to buy this place the moment I found out you were moving here.

4
00:01:51,039 --> 00:01:54,680
Thank you…for everything you’ve done for me.

5
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:57,360
You pinned the location of Sun’s dad’s house for me?

6
00:01:58,759 --> 00:01:59,840
but you, of all people…

7
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:03,000
how did you end up coming here with the general’s daughter?

8
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,600
So your schedule’s finally free these days?

9
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:07,120
That’s why you have time to come back here, huh?

10
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,759
Sun... When did you get here, sweetheart?

11
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:13,520
Jan...

12
00:02:14,160 --> 00:02:16,040
From now on, I’ll take care of Sun myself.

13
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:19,200
And I won’t let him get involved with your family again.

14
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,000
Sun, you’ve never actually been here before, right?

15
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,680
Never. Not once.

16
00:02:25,079 --> 00:02:28,200
When you said you saw me, I was surprised too.

17
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:31,640
Are you looking for me?

18
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:47,280
I won’t let anyone misunderstand you again.

19
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:52,200
Sun, come back to my room with me, please.

20
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,280
Are you looking for me?

21
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:14,760
Why do you…

22
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,160
That I do look like you?

23
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:30,880
I'm Jan. I'm your twin sisters.

24
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,640
Jan...

25
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:43,000
I think you should get going now.

26
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,440
What?

27
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,680
You look exactly alike.

28
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:57,960
I think we should get out of here first.

29
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,280
If someone sees us, this could turn into a huge mess.

30
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:02,920
Let’s go.

31
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,640
I’m coming with you.

32
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:15,920
You wouldn’t want more leaked photos of me and Phuwin, would you?

33
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,600
I don’t think he followed us.

34
00:05:02,840 --> 00:05:06,520
I was wondering why everyone in this club is dressed in black and white…

35
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:09,840
You really picked the perfect day to show up, Sun.

36
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,840
Which day are you free next week?

37
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,560
Why?

38
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:21,200
Well… you kissed me just now.
So I thought maybe you were going to take responsibility.

39
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:24,800
You know… come ask my parents for my hand. I was just about to set a date.

40
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,560
Hey, I didn’t kiss you. It was just a peck.

41
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:30,160
It was just a ‘say hi’ thing. You know… Western style.

42
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:32,480
You should be used to this by now, shouldn’t you?

43
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:41,040
I just found out that when you ‘say hi,’ Fey, you kiss on the lips.

44
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,640
Not on the cheek.

45
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:49,560
I only did that because I didn’t want you getting into trouble.

46
00:05:49,760 --> 00:05:51,360
If I’d known, I wouldn’t have helped you at all.

47
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:01,240
…Fine. Then give it back.

48
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:16,440
You haven’t gone back home at all, have you?

49
00:06:18,160 --> 00:06:20,640
You’ve been home?

50
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,000
Home...

51
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:27,080
That place… a house with no warmth like that…

52
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,920
you can even call it ‘home’?

53
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:35,800
You said you’re Sun’s twin sister.

54
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,720
So where have you been all this time?

55
00:06:39,080 --> 00:06:41,080
Why are you only showing up now?

56
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,640
This is a private family matter.

57
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,880
Does Khun Rafah really need to know?

58
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:53,080
P’Flint is just worried about me.

59
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:56,760
I deserve to know the truth too.

60
00:06:59,880 --> 00:07:03,880
As you already know, our parents divorced when we were still kids.

61
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:08,280
After that, Mom took me abroad…

62
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:10,640
and I never came back to Thailand.

63
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:13,600
Maybe it was because we were still too young back then.

64
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,760
And our parents probably never spoke about it again…

65
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,040
so neither of us knew we had a twin.

66
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,640
If you don’t believe me,

67
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:26,320
you can call General Jakarin and ask him yourself.

68
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,360
Hello, Sun.

69
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,360
I was just about to call you.

70
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,840
Really?

71
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:49,920
I actually have something important I want to ask you.

72
00:07:55,960 --> 00:07:58,920
Something important?

73
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,320
Is it about your sister, Jan?

74
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,320
My… sister? Jan?

75
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:14,920
Yes. P'Jan is your twin sister, Sun.

76
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:23,680
I’m sorry I never told you.

77
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:28,160
After your mother and I divorced,

78
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:32,080
I lost contact with both her and Jan.

79
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,600
It was my fault.

80
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:44,039
I kept thinking… maybe it would be better if you didn’t know.

81
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,720
Go ahead and be mad at me. Sun.

82
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:54,520
I’ve found P'Jan, Dad.

83
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,120
I’ll hang up for now.

84
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,880
I’ll call you again later.

85
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,200
I’m sorry, P’Jan…

86
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,720
Why are you apologizing?

87
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,480
I’m the one who should be sorry.

88
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:19,880
Ever since I came back to Thailand, I’ve only caused trouble for you.

89
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:24,280
Who would’ve thought my own twin sister would be a celebrity?

90
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,560
…Did Mom come back with you?

91
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,960
The reason I returned to Thailand…

92
00:10:39,560 --> 00:10:43,600
is because Mom had an accident. She passed away last year.

93
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:48,600
I used to think I had no one left in this world…

94
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:52,760
until I found out I still have a twin sister.

95
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:06,880
If there’s anything I can help you with, just tell me.

96
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,720
I can take care of myself.

97
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:14,480
Besides…

98
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:17,120
the person you should be most worried about right now

99
00:11:18,280 --> 00:11:20,280
is your sister.

100
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:24,640
Fey.

101
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:26,480
Sun, why don’t you stay with Khun Jan for now?

102
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:27,960
I’ll call Fey myself.

103
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,000
It’s okay.

104
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,280
I’ll call her.

105
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:35,160
I want to thank her…

106
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:38,840
and apologize, too. We left without saying anything.

107
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,840
I’ll be back in a minute, P’Jan.

108
00:11:53,120 --> 00:11:54,920
There’s something I need to talk to you.

109
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,200
Are you talking about the kiss?

110
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,720
Why are you making that face?

111
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:09,280
Or are you afraid… that I might tell my sister about it?

112
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,560
No.

113
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:14,280
I’m not afraid you’ll tell Sun.

114
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,800
Because I was planning to tell her myself anyway.

115
00:12:18,840 --> 00:12:20,840
You seem very confident…

116
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:25,160
that every woman can easily understand something like this.

117
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,760
I am confident.

118
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:31,120
I believe Sun will trust my sincerity and my honesty.

119
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,480
As for what I wanted to tell you…

120
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:38,400
I just wanted to apologize. About what happened that night.

121
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,040
I think you’ve misunderstood something.

122
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,440
Sincerity

123
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:47,920
is something you show openly…

124
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:53,440
not something you do behind someone’s back, Khun Rafah.

125
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:03,360
Wait… so you really do have a twin?

126
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:06,240
…Yeah.

127
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,560
I’ll tell you everything when we meet.

128
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:16,000
As for today… thank you. You and Khun Peach really helped a lot.

129
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:19,680
And… please apologize to her for me.

130
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:22,880
Please tell Khun Peach I’m sorry about today.

131
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:25,720
Leaving early was one thing…

132
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,680
but about the kiss...

133
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,200
That’s it. We’ll talk later.

134
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:36,920
How many times do I have to tell you? I didn’t kiss you.

135
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:41,080
Anyone who saw what you did would call that a kiss.

136
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:45,920
Oh, really? Let me tell you something. What you did that’s what counts as a kiss.

137
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,720
I haven’t even made a scene yet.

138
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,720
Go ahead. Make a scene.

139
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:51,920
I’m ready to take responsibility.

140
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:55,720
No need.

141
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,120
Just get out. Get in the car.

142
00:14:02,280 --> 00:14:05,320
You said hi already… aren’t you going to say goodbye too?

143
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:13,640
Oh, please. Just go open the car. I’m going home.

144
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,160
Hurry up.

145
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:42,520
What are you two talking about?

146
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,280
Why do you both look so serious?

147
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,360
It’s nothing, Sun.

148
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:55,120
Khun Rafah just wanted to apologize to me.

149
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,120
About what?

150
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,640
About…

151
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:07,920
not taking good care of you.

152
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:13,400
I think I should head back now.

153
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,240
You need to get some rest.

154
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,400
Then how are you getting home?

155
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,200
Should P’Flint drive you?

156
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:27,600
It’s okay. Phuwin’s waiting downstairs.

157
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,280
May I borrow it for bit.

158
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:41,720
And I hope from now on, you’ll take good care of my sister.

159
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:45,720
Don’t make her sad. Don’t make her cry again.

160
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:49,080
Because if you do…

161
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:53,440
I won’t let you off that easily.

162
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:26,839
(You are mine.)

163
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,640
Hello, Khun Mooham.

164
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:41,600
I’m sorry, Khun Rafah. I hope I’m not disturbing you.

165
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:45,280
I tried calling Sun, but her line was busy

166
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:48,480
Where are you and Sun right now?

167
00:18:50,600 --> 00:18:52,600
We’re at Sun’s room.

168
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,000
She’s in the shower.

169
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,440
I’ll let her know to call you back.

170
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:02,160
That’s okay. I’m just relieved she made it back safely.

171
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:07,080
There are photos from the club all over X right now.

172
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,600
If anyone recognized Sun,

173
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,880
from a sweet, innocent leading lady…

174
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:14,120
she’d turn into a fake image overnight.

175
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:18,760
Good thing you reacted quickly and brought her home in time.

176
00:19:43,360 --> 00:19:46,840
P’Flint, are you going to shower now? I’ll get your pajamas ready.

177
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:55,000
Is there… any other option besides showering?

178
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:05,080
No. I have an early job tomorrow.

179
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:09,360
No staying up late. Go shower.

180
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,080
There’s something I need to confess.

181
00:20:18,960 --> 00:20:20,720
Do you remember that day…

182
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:23,200
when I got back from Hong Kong?

183
00:20:23,680 --> 00:20:25,920
When I told you I ran into you at the club?

184
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,240
P’Flint, you’re back?

185
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,600
So this is how you behave when I’m not around?

186
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:38,640
Let go of me.

187
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:40,640
Don’t act innocent.

188
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:45,480
You go clubbing, you walk into men’s condos yet you’re not even ashamed.

189
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:56,520
Wait… are you saying the person you saw…

190
00:20:58,360 --> 00:20:59,680
was P’Jan?

191
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:04,200
Yes.

192
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:09,080
I’m sorry. I’ve misunderstood you all along…

193
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:13,120
even though you never lied to me.

194
00:21:14,440 --> 00:21:16,560
I’m the one who was wrong.

195
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:19,680
I even crossed the line with your sister.

196
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:23,480
Please don’t be mad at me.

197
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:30,320
Have you apologized to P’Jan yet?

198
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,960
I did.

199
00:21:36,280 --> 00:21:38,280
When you went out to call Fey.

200
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,000
But I think…

201
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:44,640
she’s still upset.

202
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:52,240
You haven’t answered me yet.

203
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:56,240
Can you forgive me?

204
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:11,160
I love you, P’Flint…

205
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:14,680
and I love P’Jan too.

206
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,520
If all of this happened because of a misunderstanding…

207
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,240
then how could I possibly stay angry at you?

208
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:26,840
Thank you… my good girl.

209
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,440
I promise

210
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:34,240
I’ll do everything I can

211
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:38,480
to make your sister accept me

212
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,880
to prove that I truly love her little sister.

213
00:23:11,280 --> 00:23:13,520
I have an early job tomorrow.

214
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:22,480
Let’s leave it for tomorrow, okay?

215
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:43,520
Breaking celebrity news shaking up the high society circle!

216
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:47,840
(A passionate kiss at a luxury club. Is this the new power couple of the elite scene?)
- Last night, eyewitnesses spotted Paabfah,

217
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:51,640
the heiress of a prominent business family, kissing Pirwaral,

218
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:55,400
the hottest hi-so photographer, at an upscale club in Thonglor.

219
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:58,560
Is this the official debut of a famous sibling duo?

220
00:23:58,560 --> 00:24:05,400
Social media is already buzzing
about the leading actress frequently appearing in the same frame…

221
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:08,840
Ugh! Why does this always happen to me?

222
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,720
Fey’s calling.

223
00:24:28,720 --> 00:24:29,560
Okay.

224
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:34,520
I was just about to call you.

225
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,240
You’ve seen the news, right?

226
00:24:36,240 --> 00:24:42,720
Of course. Mooham called me early this morning.
I’m being interviewed today about those photos.

227
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:45,240
I meant my photos.

228
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:50,560
Sun, I’ve never had a scandal like this in my life.

229
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:54,640
This is all because of that Peach.

230
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:59,000
But from the photo… it looks more like you were the one kissing her.

231
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,080
P’Flint!

232
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:07,200
I wasn’t kissing her. It was an accident. I never meant for it to look like that.

233
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:11,520
That’s it. You can stay there with your girlfriend.

234
00:25:11,720 --> 00:25:13,080
- Bye.
- Fey...

235
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:14,120
Fey...

236
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:15,680
Fey...

237
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:39,040
Khun Paabfah, there’s someone here to see you.

238
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:40,560
Sure.

239
00:25:53,320 --> 00:25:57,520
How many times do I have to tell you? I didn’t kiss you.

240
00:25:58,040 --> 00:26:00,840
What you did, anyone who saw it would call that a kiss.

241
00:26:05,880 --> 00:26:09,240
As if I’d want to kiss you. Don’t flatter yourself.

242
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:13,600
Are you thinking about my kiss right now, Khun Fey?

243
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,800
P’Flint, aren’t you afraid Fey might get upset?

244
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,400
I’m just telling the truth.

245
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:35,840
Why would I be afraid?

246
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:39,680
But I am.

247
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:43,600
What if she gets mad at you… and stops being friends with me?

248
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:46,120
What am I supposed to do?

249
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:50,120
Don’t forget, she’s my only best friend.

250
00:26:52,200 --> 00:26:56,560
Well, if she stops being your friend… you can be her sister-in-law instead.

251
00:26:57,640 --> 00:26:58,920
P’Flint!

252
00:26:59,680 --> 00:27:02,360
You don’t seem worried about the news at all.

253
00:27:02,760 --> 00:27:04,160
What news?

254
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:07,760
If it’s about Fey, maybe it’s a good thing.

255
00:27:09,000 --> 00:27:12,280
She’ll learn to be more careful.

256
00:27:15,960 --> 00:27:17,120
But…

257
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:19,800
if it’s about us…

258
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:25,840
I was planning to give an interview today.

259
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,680
To say the news isn’t true.

260
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:32,560
You don’t have to worry.

261
00:27:34,160 --> 00:27:35,400
I understand

262
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:39,800
the rumors could affect your company.

263
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,520
I’m full now.

264
00:27:58,640 --> 00:27:59,920
Who said

265
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:04,040
that I want you to tell everyone the news isn’t true?

266
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:09,280
Actually… I’d rather you tell everyone the truth.

267
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:11,880
That you’re really my girlfriend.

268
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:25,960
Oops

269
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:31,680
Uh… did I interrupt something?

270
00:28:32,040 --> 00:28:34,320
Sun told me I could come in,

271
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:35,600
so I just…

272
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:39,040
Not at all, P’Mooham. I just finished up.

273
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,440
Shall we go?

274
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:42,600
Okay.

275
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:45,520
You have a fitting today for the new drama with Nop, right?

276
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:48,960
Yes… that’s right.

277
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:53,560
But you can’t cancel or change the male lead for this one.

278
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:58,000
It’s a joint production between the network and a Korean company.

279
00:29:02,360 --> 00:29:04,160
P’Flint, you should head to work.

280
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:06,320
If the company president doesn’t show up for days,

281
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,720
your employees might start slacking off.

282
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:12,120
I’ll see you this evening.

283
00:29:13,080 --> 00:29:14,280
See you.

284
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:17,680
Let’s go.

285
00:29:35,160 --> 00:29:39,040
Hello, Khun Rafah. There’s a package delivered to you.

286
00:29:39,800 --> 00:29:42,560
But there’s no sender’s name on the box.

287
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:46,000
Security would like permission to open it for inspection.

288
00:29:48,560 --> 00:29:49,920
That’s fine.

289
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:09,880
Hey! You. Can you stop holding that bouquet?

290
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:11,800
People are staring.

291
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,360
Staring at what?

292
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:18,000
I grabbed these flowers from the sales girl.
I was just going to use them as a prop for your photos.

293
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:21,960
Or did you think I bought them for you?

294
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:25,920
Give them here.

295
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:27,800
These are for welcoming my clients.

296
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,080
Please return them to Purchasing.

297
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:32,760
Alright.

298
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:33,960
Fine.

299
00:30:34,120 --> 00:30:36,160
Next time, I’ll buy you a real one.

300
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:37,160
Hey!

301
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:45,680
Are you ready to shoot? If not, I’ll go back to work.

302
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:49,160
You’re the one who’s not ready.

303
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:54,800
You know… you’re actually pretty.

304
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:58,120
Especially when you’re not yelling.

305
00:30:58,120 --> 00:30:59,080
Excuse me?

306
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:11,840
Hey, why are you grabbing me again? That’s enough.

307
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:16,320
Are we shooting or not? Hurry.

308
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:24,200
Do you want the flowers?

309
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:26,080
Just take the photo. Quickly.

310
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:37,560
After this, you have an interview

311
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:40,600
with the press about the family dinner photo Khun Fey posted.

312
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:45,680
I haven’t forgotten. And I know exactly what you want me to say.

313
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:49,080
I understand you feel uncomfortable.

314
00:31:49,400 --> 00:31:52,240
But the network has its eyes on you right now.

315
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:55,480
About Nop… I think we should go with the flow for now.

316
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:58,760
When the timing’s right, we’ll reveal Khun Rafah.

317
00:31:59,640 --> 00:32:00,680
Let’s go.

318
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:02,800
Oh? Sun,

319
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:07,920
what a coincidence. We keep arriving at the same time.

320
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:12,200
If it happens this often, I’d call it intentional.

321
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:16,640
I heard you just had a meeting with the executives at the network.

322
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:18,160
Is something going on?

323
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:22,160
If you ever need help with anything, just tell me.

324
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:29,600
Then could you head to the dressing room now, P’Nop?

325
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:35,000
The crew’s been looking for you.

326
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:39,600
They said you’ve been here for quite a while… but haven’t gone in yet.

327
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:42,480
Let’s go.

328
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,800
P’Flint asked to see me. Is something wrong?

329
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,320
May I take a look?

330
00:33:39,640 --> 00:33:40,840
Judging from the composition…

331
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:46,280
the photographer couldn’t have been far from Khun Rafah and Sun.

332
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,200
Smile a little…

333
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:59,040
beautiful.

334
00:34:00,800 --> 00:34:03,880
At this rate, I might have to take Sun to make merit.

335
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:05,960
I don’t know why she keeps running into trouble lately.

336
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:06,920
One more shot.

337
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:08,719
Okay… got it.

338
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:10,320
That’s a wrap.

339
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:12,239
Alright, let’s go.

340
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:16,280
I think we should shoot a few more ‘moments,’.

341
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:18,280
We can send the photos to PR for promo.

342
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:24,159
Alright then. One more shot.

343
00:34:24,159 --> 00:34:25,400
Please move a little closer.

344
00:34:29,440 --> 00:34:31,840
Okay… give me a small smile.

345
00:34:32,719 --> 00:34:34,480
P’Nop, I think...

346
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:38,120
since this is the fitting for the network’s number one on-screen couple…

347
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:42,400
if we don’t give them some moments to feed the press,
the executives might be even more upset with me.

348
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:47,120
One more.

349
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:48,239
How about this?

350
00:34:53,880 --> 00:34:55,280
Beautiful.

351
00:34:58,520 --> 00:34:59,560
Ouch.

352
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:04,520
I think we’ve got enough usable shots,

353
00:35:07,080 --> 00:35:07,920
don’t you?

354
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,240
Yes.

355
00:35:16,800 --> 00:35:18,080
Let's go.

356
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,800
She’s not answering her phone.

357
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:38,320
I don’t know if she’s so upset she took Sun home already.

358
00:35:38,680 --> 00:35:41,280
JanJao, could you try calling Sun too?

359
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:42,400
Sure.

360
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:46,960
Where have you two been?

361
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:50,080
Where have you two been?

362
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:52,480
I've been calling and no one picked up.

363
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:57,960
Sorry. I left my phone in the car, so I didn’t know she called.

364
00:36:00,160 --> 00:36:04,840
Khun Rafah, I understand you’re worried about Sun.

365
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:08,040
And you don’t like Nop getting too close.

366
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:12,040
But what you did in front of the entire crew

367
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:16,040
could damage Sun’s reputation.

368
00:36:16,680 --> 00:36:20,080
I don’t care about other people’s eyes as much as I care about Sun’s feelings.

369
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:26,120
And I’ve never interfered, as long as the work stays within proper boundaries.

370
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:30,360
That’s enough. Work alone is exhausting for me.

371
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:32,760
I don’t want to listen to people arguing because of me.

372
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,640
Honestly, I think Khun Rafah has a point.

373
00:36:36,000 --> 00:36:37,520
P’Nop really did cross the line.

374
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:39,320
Even I didn’t like it.

375
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:45,320
I hired you to manage the artist not to encourage this kind of behavior.

376
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:47,760
And please call the production team

377
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:50,720
and have them delete that behind-the-scenes footage.

378
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:53,320
Yes.

379
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:57,280
Sun, I’m going to speak to the reporters first.

380
00:36:58,600 --> 00:37:01,520
Khun Rafah, please wait in the car.

381
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:11,480
Yes.

382
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:15,840
Yes, Janjao, about the footage earlier…

383
00:37:26,000 --> 00:37:28,000
P’Sun, does your head still hurt?

384
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,080
Yeah.

385
00:37:30,720 --> 00:37:32,720
I don’t know what’s going on today.

386
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:36,000
Work issues… sasaeng fans…

387
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:40,360
I really don’t understand what those people want from me.

388
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:49,760
Maybe… they just love you very much.

389
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:54,080
If that’s love, I’d rather they hate me.

390
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:02,760
Do you want to go rest first?

391
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:06,440
Our condos are close to each other.

392
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:10,320
If you don’t want to wait for the interview, I can drive you.

393
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:18,640
How do you know where I live?

394
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:23,200
I’m sure P’Mooham would never give your address to anyone.

395
00:38:24,440 --> 00:38:26,560
…You’re that sasaeng fan, aren’t you?

396
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:38,000
Ah…

397
00:38:39,120 --> 00:38:40,800
I’ve been caught.

398
00:38:43,840 --> 00:38:45,360
We were so close to finally being together.

399
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:47,080
Why are you doing this?

400
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,520
Because I love you.

401
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:58,200
I’ve watched over you.

402
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:01,040
Protected you.

403
00:39:01,040 --> 00:39:03,560
But you chose to be with someone who only causes you trouble.

404
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:06,160
Shouldn’t I be the one asking why you’re doing this?

405
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:10,400
I did everything to help you get where you are today.

406
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:13,240
I’ve loved you… since before anyone even knew your name.

407
00:39:35,720 --> 00:39:37,400
Thank you.

408
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:41,480
Numbers 105 and 106, please come inside.

409
00:39:43,480 --> 00:39:45,760
- I’ll head in first.
- Okay. Good luck.

410
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:52,720
It’s your turn. Aren’t you going in?

411
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:58,120
I’m… I’m not ready.

412
00:40:02,960 --> 00:40:04,720
Nervous?

413
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:10,680
I’ve never had this many eyes on me before. I don’t know where to look.

414
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:24,240
I understand. I was the same.

415
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:29,720
How about this if you don’t know where to look,

416
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:31,320
look at me.

417
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:34,200
I’ll be your strength.

418
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:45,040
105 and 106, you may come in now.

419
00:40:45,040 --> 00:40:46,120
Yes, we’re coming.

420
00:40:46,120 --> 00:40:47,000
Yes.

421
00:41:05,640 --> 00:41:08,160
(Announcement of selected candidates)

422
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:10,720
(Miss Atita Thitimethanan Sun)

423
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:16,120
I will watch over you and always support you, okay?

424
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:12,200
(I heard she went up to a guy’s condo, is that true?)

425
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:24,240
That’s not true! That’s not P’Sun!

426
00:42:25,560 --> 00:42:27,000
(It’s definitely Sun! / No, it’s not!)

427
00:42:27,240 --> 00:42:29,240
(Is it really Sun? / It’s definitely not P’Sun!)

428
00:42:38,400 --> 00:42:39,840
Do you see, P’Sun,

429
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:43,680
how much I’ve done for you?

430
00:42:48,680 --> 00:42:49,760
JanJao!

431
00:42:50,200 --> 00:42:52,440
JanJao! Open the door right now!

432
00:42:52,960 --> 00:42:54,960
I won’t let anyone take you away from me again.

433
00:42:57,840 --> 00:42:59,520
P’Sun has to belong to me alone.

434
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:01,440
P’Sun has to be mine only!

435
00:43:02,960 --> 00:43:04,960
JanJao! Open the door right now!

436
00:43:05,920 --> 00:43:09,320
P’Sun is mine. I won’t let anyone...

437
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:11,800
Sun! Sun!

438
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:15,600
You’re not allowed to love anyone, P’Sun!

439
00:43:15,600 --> 00:43:17,040
You have to love only your fans!

440
00:43:17,440 --> 00:43:19,160
You have to love only your fans!

441
00:43:21,720 --> 00:43:23,960
You’re my dream, P’Sun.

442
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:45,440
Even if you date someone, you’ll still love all your fans the same.

443
00:43:47,120 --> 00:43:49,080
I’ll always be right here.

444
00:43:52,040 --> 00:43:52,960
No!

445
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:55,240
I’ll deal with everyone who caused this problem!

446
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:56,880
Let me go! Let me go!

447
00:43:57,280 --> 00:43:58,840
Let me go!

448
00:43:59,520 --> 00:44:01,920
Take her away. Take her away!

449
00:44:01,920 --> 00:44:03,080
How’s your feeling now?

450
00:44:03,080 --> 00:44:04,520
Please take care of this for me.

451
00:44:04,520 --> 00:44:05,240
Okay.

452
00:44:06,200 --> 00:44:08,360
Sun, Are you okay?

453
00:44:08,760 --> 00:44:10,400
Oh my goodness!

454
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:16,840
Let me go! I’m not going! Let me go!

455
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:19,760
Let me go! I’m not going! Let me go!

456
00:44:19,760 --> 00:44:23,400
Let me go! Let me go!

457
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:27,120
You have no right to detain me without any evidence.

458
00:44:28,360 --> 00:44:31,040
I guess you don’t know that this studio has CCTV cameras.

459
00:44:33,360 --> 00:44:35,760
I think it’s better not to make this a big issue.

460
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:37,640
Because if you hurt Fey,

461
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:41,320
I won’t stop at just having you put on probation.

462
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:44,000
Please take care of it.

463
00:44:44,280 --> 00:44:45,120
Yes.

464
00:44:45,760 --> 00:44:48,120
Let me go! Let me go, I’m not going!

465
00:44:48,120 --> 00:44:51,520
Let me go! I’m not going! Let go!

466
00:44:52,440 --> 00:44:53,920
I’m not going!

467
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:05,080
Are you okay?

468
00:45:05,080 --> 00:45:06,200
Okay.

469
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:07,680
Peach, are you okay?

470
00:45:08,160 --> 00:45:08,880
I’m okay.

471
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:10,640
Is there some kind of problem here?

472
00:45:14,120 --> 00:45:17,440
Whether there is or not, do I have to report it to you?

473
00:45:18,720 --> 00:45:20,360
Let’s go.

474
00:45:21,040 --> 00:45:23,040
No need to inform me.

475
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:28,080
I’m just concerned. I’m worried you might cause more trouble for Sun.

476
00:45:31,480 --> 00:45:33,440
Before you say anything,

477
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:36,320
maybe you should take a look at yourself first.

478
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:49,080
Are you alright?

479
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:56,600
Is everything settled, Fey?

480
00:45:56,720 --> 00:45:58,440
Yes, it’s settled.

481
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:03,280
I’m really worried about you, Sun. You keep running into one problem after another.

482
00:46:03,280 --> 00:46:06,640
Just now, I even dealt with that “shipping-obsessed” guy of yours.

483
00:46:06,880 --> 00:46:08,960
Something about his face just doesn’t seem trustworthy.

484
00:46:09,520 --> 00:46:11,760
Who knows what kind of surprise drama he might stir up for you again?

485
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:17,760
Thank you so much.

486
00:46:26,040 --> 00:46:27,880
What is going on here?

487
00:46:30,080 --> 00:46:33,760
This is P’Jan, My twin sister.

488
00:46:39,200 --> 00:46:41,960
Hello. You must be…

489
00:46:41,960 --> 00:46:44,760
Khun Fey, Sun’s close friend, right?

490
00:46:48,640 --> 00:46:49,920
And you...

491
00:46:50,360 --> 00:46:53,520
Nice to see you again, Khun Peach.

492
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:58,120
If I remember correctly, you still haven’t returned my lipstick.

493
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:01,520
See? I told you I’m not a psycho.

494
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:07,200
Hello, P’Jan. Nice to meet you.

495
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:12,600
When I first found out Sun had a twin, I was shocked.

496
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,840
But after meeting you, I’m even more shocked.

497
00:47:16,400 --> 00:47:17,560
I didn’t think..

498
00:47:18,520 --> 00:47:20,200
You’d look this identical.

499
00:47:21,440 --> 00:47:23,000
I’m surprised too

500
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:27,360
that you seem much cuter than someone like Khun Rafah, the older sister.

501
00:47:30,720 --> 00:47:34,000
Um… then how did Khun Rafah know

502
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:36,280
that Nong JanJao was the sasaeng fan?

503
00:47:38,480 --> 00:47:40,480
At first, I only suspected it.

504
00:47:41,160 --> 00:47:45,560
About what Sun said that Khun Mooham was the one who told JanJao to call

505
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:49,240
regarding the account that announced a cash giveaway
in exchange for Sun's photos at the pub.

506
00:47:49,520 --> 00:47:52,040
But when Khun Mooham called me,

507
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:55,680
she spoke as if she had never known anything about it.

508
00:47:57,960 --> 00:48:01,800
What really made me certain that she was the sasaeng

509
00:48:03,400 --> 00:48:05,680
was when I saw JanJao’s phone cast.

510
00:48:10,560 --> 00:48:11,720
yes.

511
00:48:12,040 --> 00:48:14,040
Um… are you from the staff?

512
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:17,080
Where are you going?

513
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:22,880
I’m sorry.

514
00:48:22,920 --> 00:48:23,600
It’s okay.

515
00:48:26,600 --> 00:48:27,880
Here.

516
00:48:28,240 --> 00:48:30,240
This is the CCTV footage, P’Flint.

517
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:54,480
So observant just like you, P’Flint.

518
00:48:55,280 --> 00:48:57,320
That makes me feel relieved,

519
00:48:57,320 --> 00:49:00,680
knowing that my friend will be well taken care of by you.

520
00:49:13,280 --> 00:49:15,280
Thank you, P’Flint.

521
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:17,560
Yes.

522
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:26,600
Hello, good afternoon.

523
00:49:27,760 --> 00:49:29,840
Oh yes, Sun is ready.

524
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:31,560
Okay.

525
00:49:32,920 --> 00:49:35,600
Sun, the reporters are calling you for the interview.

526
00:49:40,840 --> 00:49:42,840
It seems like...

527
00:49:43,560 --> 00:49:50,320
you’ll have to return my younger sister to her on-screen partner now, Khun Rafah.

528
00:50:03,240 --> 00:50:06,280
So, sis. who’s going to play the villain in this drama?

529
00:50:06,280 --> 00:50:08,280
Exactly, we still don’t know yet.

530
00:50:08,920 --> 00:50:10,200
Hello, everyone.

531
00:50:10,200 --> 00:50:11,720
Oh, MooHam!

532
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:15,080
Excuse me, may I let Sun change outfits for a moment?

533
00:50:15,080 --> 00:50:18,280
Of course. But… don’t take this the wrong way

534
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:20,480
- What is it?
- Let me gossip a little.

535
00:50:20,480 --> 00:50:23,040
So who’s going to play the villain in this series?

536
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:25,320
We’ve all been guessing like crazy.

537
00:50:25,520 --> 00:50:28,080
Honestly, I don’t know either. But

538
00:50:28,080 --> 00:50:31,920
if she’s pairing up with Sun and Nop, it has to be a big name for sure.

539
00:50:31,920 --> 00:50:32,920
Who could it be?

540
00:50:32,920 --> 00:50:34,720
- Is she older? Give us a little hint.
- Who do you think it is?

541
00:50:34,720 --> 00:50:35,960
- Yes
- Who?

542
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:40,640
It’s time. Who will take on the leading role in this project?

543
00:50:41,360 --> 00:50:43,640
Are you excited?

544
00:50:55,680 --> 00:51:02,200
Someone once said that the sun always shines brightly after the storm passes.

545
00:51:02,960 --> 00:51:04,400
For me…

546
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:06,920
no matter how many more storms I have to face,

547
00:51:08,160 --> 00:51:10,120
as long as P’Flint is still here…

548
00:51:10,920 --> 00:51:13,440
I won’t be afraid of anything anymore.

549
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:35,240
Congratulations.

550
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:48,360
It’s been a long time, hasn’t it, Flint?

551
00:52:41,360 --> 00:52:42,800
Dear, Diary.

552
00:52:43,560 --> 00:52:45,760
Today was the first time in my life I went to an audition.

553
00:52:46,120 --> 00:52:49,200
Everything was so new. I was really excited.

554
00:52:49,800 --> 00:52:53,200
But I tried my best to memorize the script and perform as well as I could.

555
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:57,600
I just realized that inspiration from someone

556
00:52:57,600 --> 00:53:01,480
can be powerful enough to make a shy person like me

557
00:53:01,480 --> 00:53:04,120
stand in front of a camera to audition like this.

558
00:53:04,920 --> 00:53:07,680
Please cheer me on, P’Flint.

559
00:53:09,480 --> 00:53:11,480
That day, Sun went as my girlfriend.

560
00:53:11,480 --> 00:53:12,160
What…?

561
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:16,560
You’re talking as if you’re worried about me.

562
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:20,360
Well, since you don’t worry about yourself, I have to worry about you instead.

563
00:53:20,560 --> 00:53:23,760
Does Khun Rafah know that Sun was summoned by the executives?

564
00:53:23,880 --> 00:53:26,800
At the very least, Sun should make her aware

565
00:53:27,080 --> 00:53:29,800
that what he’s doing might cause trouble for her.

566
00:53:30,480 --> 00:53:33,120
And if any more problems happen after this,

567
00:53:33,680 --> 00:53:36,840
I may have to replace the person in charge of taking care of Sun.

568
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:38,200
Congratulations.

569
00:53:40,200 --> 00:53:42,200
It’s been a long time, hasn’t it, Flint?

570
00:53:43,040 --> 00:53:46,080
But still, you and P’Ya used to date.

571
00:53:46,640 --> 00:53:49,880
So it’s not strange if P’Ya calls you, right?

572
00:53:50,720 --> 00:53:53,520
You haven’t forgotten why we broke up, have you?

573
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:56,520
Just be careful not to let history repeat itself.

574
00:53:56,680 --> 00:53:58,760
As for the villain role everyone’s been wondering about

575
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:03,360
it’s me.
